Facts (layer 2):

`x :: Number` (ConstantDefinition):
  has definition constraints
  has type `Number` or `String`
  is a definition

`Number` (NamedType):
  has type `Number` or `String`
  is a type
  resolved to 1 definition(s): `Number : type`
  type is annotated

`x : "42"` (AssignmentStatement):
  has type `()`

`"42"` (StringExpression):
  has type `Number` or `String`
  is an expression
  type is annotated



Feedback:

`x :: Number` (conflicting-types)

  `x :: Number` is a `Number` or a `String`, but it can only be one of these.
  
  `x :: Number` must be the same type as `"42"` and `Number`; double-check these.
